      <hedline>
        <hl1>Harold Levy's Task</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kimberly Wadsworth letter holds interim schools chancellor Harold O Levy should be working on intellectual enrichment of New York City students, not of Board of Education</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Schools Chief Plays Higgins to Unlikely Eliza, the School Board'' (front page, May 2):</p>
        <p>You report that Harold O. Levy, the interim schools chancellor, is sponsoring splashy events like a lecture on cosmology and a violin lesson with Isaac Stern, for the intellectual enrichment of the members of the Board of Education.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Schools Chief Plays Higgins to Unlikely Eliza, the School Board'' (front page, May 2):</p>
        <p>You report that Harold O. Levy, the interim schools chancellor, is sponsoring splashy events like a lecture on cosmology and a violin lesson with Isaac Stern, for the intellectual enrichment of the members of the Board of Education.</p>
        <p>Do I misunderstand his job duties, or is he not supposed to be working on the intellectual enrichment of New York City's public school students?</p>
        <p>KIMBERLY  WADSWORTH  New York, May 3, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
